A vintage 1960s-style illustration of two young Asian boys in school uniforms sitting at a wooden desk at home, hunched over an early bulky computer monitor displaying colorful geometric shapes. Through the window behind them, tropical rain pours down on palm trees and colonial-style buildings. The room is warmly lit with a retro desk lamp casting amber shadows. Scattered around the desk are loose papers, pencils, and an old rotary telephone. The boys wear expressions of curious concentration mixed with slight frustration. The color palette features warm sepia tones, muted teals, and faded oranges typical of vintage Singaporean photography and illustration from the mid-20th century. The composition has a nostalgic, documentary quality capturing the awkward early days of technology meeting traditional education.
